%section.why
	.why-container
		.content
			%h2 Why Magnetic Tracking?
			.intro
				%p Magnetic motion tracking clearly has undisputed advantages over other tracking models. Polhemus uses proprietary AC electromagnetic tracking technology because of the advantages it offers over pulsed DC magnetic tracking. Polhemus originated the DC concept but elected not to pursue it because of overall performance penalties. Some of the strengths of Polhemus Magnetic Tracking are listed below:	
			.cross.white.cross-tl
			.cross.yellow.cross-tr
			.cross.white.cross-br
			.cross.yellow.cross-bl
			
		.list
			.item No LOS (Line-of-Sight) optical occlusion constraints as you would see in optical tracking
			.item 6 Degree-Of-Freedom measurements (x, y, z; yaw, pitch, roll) is native to our technology
			.item No acoustic constraints as would be seen in DC Magnetic or Ultrasonic Tracking
			.item Enables real-time measurement of trainee orientation
			.item No IR or thermal limitations typically associated with lens-based systems
			.item Measurement accuracy is precise and repeatable
			.item No drift characteristics as would be seen in tracking system using inertial gyros – Polhemus provides repeatable results every time
			.item No user calibration is required in most environments
			.item Fast – Polhemus LIBERTY™ has a 240Hz update rate for all sensors running simultaneously
			.item Does not require scrutiny of wideband RF interference impact by spectrum authority
			.item Does not require RF transmission regulatory exception in the US and elsewhere
		
	
